In `@apps/web-e2e/src/onboarding-ai-hero.spec.ts` around lines 5 - 20, After
navigating to the onboarding page via await page.goto('/en/onboarding'), add an
axe-core accessibility assertion before or immediately after the existing
visibility checks (i.e., near the existing expects for the headings and AI
label). Call your project's axe helper (for example runAxe(page) or
expect(page).toHaveNoViolations()) right after the page.goto('/en/onboarding')
line to run the axe scan and fail the test on violations; ensure the import/use
matches your test helpers.
