_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🔴 Critical_ | _🏗️ Heavy lift_

**Do not trust model-supplied `onboarding_last_user_text` for write confirmation.**

Line 65/Line 66 currently verifies confirmation from tool args, which the model can fabricate. That allows bypassing explicit-user-confirmation for a write action. Confirmation must be derived from trusted server-side conversation history (latest actual user turn), not from schema input.  


<details>
<summary>Suggested direction</summary>

```diff
 const inputSchema = z.object({
   space_slug: z.string().trim().min(1),
@@
-  onboarding_last_user_text: z.string().optional(),
   require_confirmation_token: z
@@
 export function createUpdateSpaceSettingsTool(authToken: string) {
+  // Inject trusted latest user text from server-side chat state/context.
+  return function withTrustedContext(lastUserText: string | null) {
   return {
@@
-      const confirmed = hasExplicitConfirmation(
-        data.onboarding_last_user_text,
-        confirmationToken,
-      );
+      const confirmed = hasExplicitConfirmation(lastUserText, confirmationToken);
@@
   } satisfies ChatRouteTool<typeof inputSchema>;
+  };
 }
```

</details>


